  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A cross-sectional sampling of males makes reproductive senescence harder to detect, especially if low-quality males selectively disappear 55, 56.",
    "Cross-sectional studies might thus underestimate male reproductive senescence, compared to the longitudinal sampling of the same males at different ages 103.",
    "Manipulations* Manipulated environments that are outside of what healthy organisms typically experience, such as environments with stressful conditions, can exacerbate reproductive senescence 104.",
    "Thus, males exposed to manipulations such as thermal stress, poor diet, or toxins could be more likely to show reproductive senescence than males not subjected to these stressors.",
    "Other manipulations, such as experimental inbreeding 105 or selection for deleterious mutations 106, may exacerbate reproductive senescence."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
